    <note>Pi(1) Gongbi [1405] His father (or kin), Zhongrong [3701] (Ziliang's [7314] son], was intendant for mines and mints in Shenxi in 1040-44 (XCB, 129.9a, 146.15a). Yanzhong's [1406] father, Zhao(1) Zhongmo's [3195] [imperial clan] son-in-law. In 1071, Gongbi was given the right to select his own subordinates in the office of Intendant of Exchange, as had his predecessor, Xue(1) Xiang [800]. XCB, 203.16b, 219.7a, 221.13a, 222.14a-14b, 229.4b, 243.13b-14a, 246.17a, 259.12b, 260.45a, 274.1b-2a, 277.9a, 278.1b, 280.17b, 288.8b, 297.12b, 16b; XCBSB, 6.12a; SHY:ZG, 43.2b-3a, 5b, 65.28a. CBD, 1, 517.</note>
